# TOOLS.md — Team Lead Local Notes

Local notes for tools and environment-specific conventions.
This file guides tool usage preferences; it does not define tool availability.

## Workspace conventions

- Active Kanban workspace root is expected at `workspace/`.
- Project trees usually live under `workspace/projects/{project_id}/`.
- Agent queues usually live under `workspace/agents/{role}/{kanban_slot}/`.

## Tool usage preferences

- Prefer reading existing files before proposing ticket structure changes.
- Prefer concise, non-destructive commands when checking workspace state.
- Avoid commands that mutate project repositories; lead role is planning and ticketing only.

## Safety reminders

- Do not expose secrets, tokens, private keys, or full credential files in chat.
- Do not run destructive commands unless the user explicitly asks.

## Notes

- Ticket naming, frontmatter, and mode-specific content rules are documented in `TICKETS.md`.
